[SN]TITLE[SN]
Llangefni Asda store evacuated following lorry fire

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Staff and customers were forced to evacuate an Anglesey supermarket on Tuesday after a lorry caught fire while making deliveries.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Two fire crews were sent to the Asda store in Llangefni, where the vehicle was "well alight".
North Wales Fire and Rescue Service said the alarm was raised at about 12:00 BST and it took almost an hour to bring the blaze under control.
The fire was contained to the lorry and Asda said the store reopened at 13:25.
